{
  "texts": [
    "Well-known examples include VADER and LIWC (19).",
    "The overall sentiment of a text is typically calculated by aggregating the scores of its individual words, with some methods adjusting for linguistic features such as negation or intensification.",
    "As shown in Figure 2, these lexicon-based approaches were applied in 4 of the reviewed studies.",
    "Compared to machine learning approaches, lexicon-based methods are valued for their simplicity, interpretability, and lower computational demands.",
    "They do not require large labeled training datasets, making them practical for initial analyses or in settings with limited resources."
  ]
}